1
00:00:03,156 --> 00:00:07,497
What? Ran, you're the
strongest in the karate club?

2
00:00:07,664 --> 00:00:09,835
That's right, Yasuko.

3
00:00:09,919 --> 00:00:12,424
She can send the boys
flying with one kick.

4
00:00:12,507 --> 00:00:13,843
Wait... hold on, Yayoi.

5
00:00:13,927 --> 00:00:15,096
That's going too far.

6
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:18,102
Wow, a real karate master.
- Yasuko Kawakami (25), sharehouse resident / office lady.

7
00:00:18,186 --> 00:00:20,190
No, not really.

8
00:00:20,523 --> 00:00:22,736
As a fellow member of the karate club...
- Yayoi Yajima (21), sharehouse resident / university student

9
00:00:22,819 --> 00:00:24,365
I'm so proud.

10
00:00:24,448 --> 00:00:27,454
Oh no, look at the time.

11
00:00:27,997 --> 00:00:29,708
I need to take my bath.

12
00:00:29,792 --> 00:00:31,754
Then I should be going too...

13
00:00:31,837 --> 00:00:34,426
Aw, you came all this way
to visit...

14
00:00:34,510 --> 00:00:35,845
Stay a little longer.

15
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:37,474
Someone's picking you up, right?

16
00:00:37,557 --> 00:00:38,936
Yes, well...

17
00:00:39,228 --> 00:00:42,776
Then it's fine. We finally
got to know each other.

18
00:00:42,859 --> 00:00:44,822
That's right.
I'm home.

19
00:00:45,115 --> 00:00:47,494
Oh, welcome back, Suzuki.

20
00:00:47,577 --> 00:00:48,705
I'm back.

21
00:00:48,788 --> 00:00:51,335
This is my junior from school,
Ran Mouri.

22
00:00:51,877 --> 00:00:53,339
Sorry to intrude.

23
00:00:53,423 --> 00:00:55,260
Hello, I'm Suzuki.
- Hidehisa Suzuki (26), sharehouse resident / company employee.

24
00:00:55,802 --> 00:00:58,808
Oh, Suzuki, would you
like some cake too?

25
00:01:00,186 --> 00:01:03,276
You sure? I'm the peeping tom,
you know.

26
00:01:03,359 --> 00:01:04,361
What?

27
00:01:04,946 --> 00:01:07,659
Nobody believes that, you know.

28
00:01:07,743 --> 00:01:11,834
It's best 15 minutes out of the
fridge, so wait a little.

29
00:01:12,252 --> 00:01:13,713
(Katsuko Kanou) I'm home.

30
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:15,842
Welcome back.

31
00:01:21,103 --> 00:01:23,942
Oh, Suzuki, you're still here?
- Katsuko Kano (25), sharehouse resident / dancer.

32
00:01:24,026 --> 00:01:25,905
Didn't the landlord
tell you something?

33
00:01:25,988 --> 00:01:27,491
To get out, and soon?

34
00:01:27,909 --> 00:01:29,745
You're the one who lied.

35
00:01:29,828 --> 00:01:31,624
Saying I was a peeping tom.

36
00:01:31,707 --> 00:01:34,421
Because it's easier in
lots of ways with just us girls.

37
00:01:34,505 --> 00:01:35,507
Don't be ridiculous.

38
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:38,137
We have a guest, you know.

39
00:01:38,221 --> 00:01:40,058
Please stop, Katsuko.

40
00:01:40,558 --> 00:01:44,817
Oh, Yayoi, dear.
You're one to talk to me?

41
00:01:45,401 --> 00:01:46,695
Well, never mind.

42
00:01:46,905 --> 00:01:49,660
I need to practice my
tap dancing before my bath.

43
00:01:49,743 --> 00:01:52,541
Um, Katsuko...
What?

44
00:01:53,042 --> 00:01:56,967
I've said it before, but could you
ease up on the tap practice?

45
00:01:57,634 --> 00:02:01,851
My room is right below yours,
remember? So...

46
00:02:02,435 --> 00:02:06,903
Oh, there's cake.
You like it, don't you, Katsuko?

47
00:02:07,445 --> 00:02:09,825
Oh, buttering me up?
No, it's not that...

48
00:02:09,909 --> 00:02:11,829
I'll have some later, then.

49
00:02:16,547 --> 00:02:18,885
(door opens and closes)

50
00:02:18,969 --> 00:02:20,680
Phew. Well then...

51
00:02:20,763 --> 00:02:22,977
- I'm off to the bath.
- Okay.

52
00:02:23,436 --> 00:02:27,444
I'm sorry, Ran. You had to
see us at our worst.

53
00:02:27,736 --> 00:02:30,617
Oh... no.
Hm?

54
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,621
Oh, it's fine.

55
00:02:32,955 --> 00:02:35,418
Suzuki would never
do any peeping.

56
00:02:36,128 --> 00:02:39,259
Katsuko just spread that
rumor on her own.

57
00:02:39,343 --> 00:02:41,055
Enough about that.

58
00:02:41,889 --> 00:02:46,023
I'll settle things with
that woman properly later.

59
00:02:46,690 --> 00:02:49,404
Thanks for the cake.
I'll eat it in my room.

60
00:02:49,488 --> 00:02:53,496
- Take it easy, then.
-  Oh, thanks.

61
00:02:59,216 --> 00:03:00,970
A refreshing autumn breeze blows through

62
00:03:01,053 --> 00:03:02,722
the gaiety of summer for a stylish and dashing display
of deduction.

63
00:03:02,806 --> 00:03:06,230
A shocking case in a shared house...
What is this calculated alibi trick?

64
00:03:06,605 --> 00:03:08,025
Seeing through the one and only truth.

65
00:03:08,109 --> 00:03:09,736
Looks like a child but has the mind of an adult.

66
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:12,367
His name is Detective Conan!

67
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:19,465
♪~

68
00:04:47,641 --> 00:04:53,653
~♪

76
00:04:55,819 --> 00:05:01,019
"The Blind Spot in the Share House"

69
00:05:01,126 --> 00:05:04,508
There's a lot to it,
share houses too.

70
00:05:04,591 --> 00:05:07,597
When I first came here,
I thought it was so stylish.

71
00:05:08,181 --> 00:05:11,939
Even the door to this common space
is made of glass.

72
00:05:12,022 --> 00:05:14,611
And there are potted
plants set out.

73
00:05:15,028 --> 00:05:19,120
It's been renovated so anyone can
come in here without hesitation.

74
00:05:19,788 --> 00:05:22,627
Well, we are living with
complete strangers.

75
00:05:23,170 --> 00:05:25,382
So there's plenty of stress too.

76
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:27,303
And there are all kinds of rules.

77
00:05:27,386 --> 00:05:29,348
- Rules?
- Yes.

78
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,352
Take a look at the back
of the chair.

79
00:05:32,354 --> 00:05:33,356
Oh.

80
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:37,156
Like putting name stickers
on your own belongings.

81
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:39,661
It's true.
(door slides open)

82
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:42,166
Ah, that was a nice bath.

83
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:45,507
- Well, I'll go in now.
- Okay.

84
00:05:46,049 --> 00:05:47,844
So, what were you two talking about?

85
00:05:48,386 --> 00:05:52,729
Gossip about you, Yayoi. Like how you
always forget to take out the trash.

86
00:05:53,396 --> 00:05:55,150
Ha, I just slip up sometimes.

87
00:05:55,234 --> 00:05:59,535
I hear there are set times for
cleaning duty and baths too.

88
00:05:59,868 --> 00:06:03,333
And even a message board.
Sounds tough.

89
00:06:03,417 --> 00:06:08,218
Yeah, but compared to the going rate,
the rent here is really cheap.

90
00:06:08,301 --> 00:06:10,305
So nobody wants to leave.

91
00:06:10,389 --> 00:06:13,938
Huh.
(phone ringing)

92
00:06:14,773 --> 00:06:19,323
Ah, Yasuko?
Katsuko's cake?

93
00:06:19,908 --> 00:06:22,747
Yes, yes.

94
00:06:22,831 --> 00:06:25,587
If she doesn't come within 15 minutes,
I'll put it back.

95
00:06:25,670 --> 00:06:28,091
(ticking of a clock)

96
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,515
Yayoi, let me help you.

97
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:35,230
It's fine, just the dishes.
You're a guest.

98
00:06:36,483 --> 00:06:39,615
- Huh?
- Is something wrong?

99
00:06:39,698 --> 00:06:41,284
No, nothing.

100
00:06:45,042 --> 00:06:49,885
Um, did something happen
with that Katsuko person?

101
00:06:50,344 --> 00:06:53,308
She never came for the cake,
Katsuko.

102
00:06:53,391 --> 00:06:55,312
(ticking of a clock)

103
00:07:00,949 --> 00:07:04,623
I owe that woman money.

104
00:07:04,957 --> 00:07:08,171
- Money?
- Yeah.

105
00:07:10,175 --> 00:07:11,512
I see.

106
00:07:11,804 --> 00:07:14,225
Since your father suddenly passed away...

107
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:18,316
And my little brother's still in
middle school, so it costs money.

108
00:07:18,401 --> 00:07:20,780
I can't ask them to send
me much from home.

109
00:07:21,364 --> 00:07:23,034
But it's okay.

110
00:07:23,118 --> 00:07:26,207
For now, I'm getting by with
scholarships and part-time work.

111
00:07:26,290 --> 00:07:28,587
Oh...
(door slides open)

112
00:07:28,879 --> 00:07:31,802
Oh... Katsuko never came.

113
00:07:31,885 --> 00:07:33,848
Really? That woman...

114
00:07:33,931 --> 00:07:36,102
So selfish.
(doorbell)

115
00:07:36,185 --> 00:07:40,570
Oh, could that be...
Your ride. Coming.

116
00:07:40,903 --> 00:07:43,324
(Kogoro Mouri)
Sorry to trouble you.

117
00:07:43,409 --> 00:07:45,078
Keeping her out this late.

118
00:07:45,162 --> 00:07:46,582
Ran, let's go home.

119
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:50,213
Yayoi, Yasuko,
thank you so much.

120
00:07:50,297 --> 00:07:52,259
- Come visit again.
- Okay.

121
00:07:52,342 --> 00:07:54,221
Aaah!

122
00:07:57,729 --> 00:08:00,443
What's wrong? What happened?
Suzuki?

123
00:08:01,445 --> 00:08:04,366
Inside... Ka... Katsuko is...

124
00:08:06,997 --> 00:08:10,505
(three people screaming)

125
00:08:13,469 --> 00:08:16,809
(Wataru Takagi)
The victim is Katsuko Kanou, 25.

126
00:08:17,685 --> 00:08:21,401
The weapon is the knife found at the
scene, no doubt about it...

127
00:08:21,777 --> 00:08:24,115
but there were no fingerprints on it.

128
00:08:24,198 --> 00:08:29,250
The estimated time of death is
between 7:15 and 7:45 PM.

129
00:08:30,210 --> 00:08:32,214
And on the floor at the scene...

130
00:08:32,297 --> 00:08:34,427
from the contents of a plastic
bottle that had rolled there...

131
00:08:34,761 --> 00:08:37,307
sleeping pills were detected.

132
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:41,023
I see. So she was
stabbed after being knocked out.

133
00:08:41,692 --> 00:08:46,869
Now, Suzuki, you found the body.
Tell us how it happened.

134
00:08:47,202 --> 00:08:48,414
Oh, yes.

135
00:08:48,497 --> 00:08:52,212
This morning, Katsuko left a
message for me...

136
00:08:52,296 --> 00:08:54,801
on that message board over there.

137
00:08:54,885 --> 00:08:58,308
"Tonight before 8, I'll come
to your room."

138
00:08:58,391 --> 00:09:00,395
"Let's settle things," it said.

139
00:09:00,813 --> 00:09:04,404
Hm? There's nothing
written there at all.

140
00:09:04,487 --> 00:09:07,242
Did anyone else
see this message?

141
00:09:07,619 --> 00:09:10,332
It said, "Keep it a secret."

142
00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:13,254
So I erased it myself. 

143
00:09:13,589 --> 00:09:15,300
And I'm always the last...

144
00:09:15,383 --> 00:09:19,058
one to leave the house, so
Katsuko probably...

145
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,519
waited until I'd be...

146
00:09:20,603 --> 00:09:23,233
- alone before writing it.
- And then?

147
00:09:23,984 --> 00:09:27,617
Just like the message said, I waited
in my room the whole time. But...

148
00:09:28,619 --> 00:09:30,915
even past 8, Katsuko
didn't come...

149
00:09:31,708 --> 00:09:33,837
so I went to her room...

150
00:09:34,714 --> 00:09:37,386
and Katsuko was on the bed...

151
00:09:37,845 --> 00:09:39,139
I see.

152
00:09:39,223 --> 00:09:41,687
It's true. Please believe me.

153
00:09:51,707 --> 00:09:53,167
No... that's wrong.

154
00:09:53,794 --> 00:09:55,338
I didn't do it.

155
00:09:56,048 --> 00:09:57,301
That's right.

156
00:09:57,384 --> 00:09:59,305
Yayoi, Yasuko.

157
00:10:00,056 --> 00:10:04,356
Oh, do you two have some
idea about this?

158
00:10:07,989 --> 00:10:12,415
The truth is, Katsuko and Suzuki
have been fighting nonstop lately.

159
00:10:12,498 --> 00:10:16,923
Tonight too, before they went to their
rooms, they got into a bit of an argument.

160
00:10:17,592 --> 00:10:19,929
- Ran, is that true?
- Yeah.

161
00:10:20,221 --> 00:10:21,433
It's not just me.

162
00:10:21,516 --> 00:10:23,394
Yasuko and Yayoi...

163
00:10:23,479 --> 00:10:25,524
both hated Katsuko too.

164
00:10:25,941 --> 00:10:27,277
Please wait.

165
00:10:27,361 --> 00:10:29,741
I don't think those two
are connected to this.

166
00:10:30,241 --> 00:10:32,955
Ran, how do you know that?

167
00:10:33,039 --> 00:10:37,548
Between 7 and 8, were those two
in the bath right on schedule?

168
00:10:38,132 --> 00:10:40,261
They were here with me.

169
00:10:40,596 --> 00:10:42,182
On schedule?

170
00:10:42,265 --> 00:10:44,144
- It's all set.
- Huh?

171
00:10:44,604 --> 00:10:47,944
The bath times.
It's a share house, after all.

172
00:10:48,236 --> 00:10:52,327
Right. And aside from getting
up once for the bathroom...

173
00:10:52,412 --> 00:10:55,166
I was sitting here the whole time.

174
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:59,049
From here, you can see the
hallway through the glass door.

175
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:01,471
A sliding glass door.

176
00:11:01,888 --> 00:11:03,600
You can see right through it.

177
00:11:04,101 --> 00:11:06,440
To get from the bath
to the second floor...

178
00:11:06,523 --> 00:11:09,654
you absolutely have to pass
through that hallway.

179
00:11:09,904 --> 00:11:12,493
During the time Yasuko
was in the bath...

180
00:11:12,577 --> 00:11:14,747
nobody passed by, I'm sure of it.

181
00:11:15,165 --> 00:11:18,714
I see. So both of them
have alibis. 
182
00:11:19,424 --> 00:11:24,349
Now, Suzuki, I'm sorry, but
at the scene on the second floor...

183
00:11:24,434 --> 00:11:26,813
could you explain once more...

184
00:11:26,897 --> 00:11:29,736
- the situation when you found her?
- Yes.

185
00:11:30,821 --> 00:11:34,077
"Write your name on
personal items," huh...

186
00:11:35,288 --> 00:11:39,506
Come to think of it, the bottle at the
scene had a name on it too.

187
00:11:40,591 --> 00:11:44,306
- Want something to drink?
- Oh... no, I'm fine.

188
00:11:44,389 --> 00:11:46,352
Don't be shy.

189
00:11:46,436 --> 00:11:49,024
Hey, was that cake Katsuko's?

190
00:11:49,859 --> 00:11:53,282
That's right. I took it out of the
fridge and got it ready.

191
00:11:54,201 --> 00:11:56,998
Yasuko called from the bath...

192
00:11:57,082 --> 00:11:58,877
since she was undressed.

193
00:11:59,044 --> 00:12:02,300
But in the end she never
came to eat it, Katsuko.

194
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,306
So I put it back in the fridge.

195
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:08,689
It's best 15 minutes out
of the fridge.

196
00:12:08,772 --> 00:12:11,318
I wanted her to eat it when
it was tastiest.

197
00:12:13,615 --> 00:12:14,826
I see.

198
00:12:15,494 --> 00:12:17,330
Something wrong, Conan?

199
00:12:17,707 --> 00:12:19,084
Oh, no.

200
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:21,590
Was there anything else strange?

201
00:12:21,673 --> 00:12:23,217
Anything strange?

202
00:12:24,721 --> 00:12:26,140
Oh, now that I mention it...

203
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:29,439
Yayoi, when you were
doing the dishes...

204
00:12:29,522 --> 00:12:31,901
- you tilted your head, didn't you?
- Hm?

205
00:12:32,277 --> 00:12:34,156
Yayoi, let me help.

206
00:12:34,239 --> 00:12:37,788
It's fine, just the dishes.
You're a guest.

207
00:12:38,790 --> 00:12:39,792
Huh?

208
00:12:40,209 --> 00:12:44,469
Ah, normally when someone's
in the bath...

209
00:12:44,552 --> 00:12:49,311
the water pressure gets weaker, but at
that time it was running normally.

210
00:12:49,394 --> 00:12:52,025
Oh, the bath was that way, right?

211
00:12:52,401 --> 00:12:54,029
Hey, wait, Conan.

212
00:13:05,803 --> 00:13:07,682
Oh, here too.

213
00:13:08,307 --> 00:13:10,854
A wiped spot and a footprint.

214
00:13:10,938 --> 00:13:12,190
What's the matter?

215
00:13:12,733 --> 00:13:15,823
Hey, what's this?

216
00:13:15,906 --> 00:13:20,833
Huh? Oh, no, that's shampoo.

217
00:13:20,916 --> 00:13:24,507
When I refilled it with a new one today,
I spilled some.

218
00:13:24,882 --> 00:13:28,473
I thought I'd wiped it up nicely,
but I guess I missed a spot.

219
00:13:33,357 --> 00:13:34,359
The window.

220
00:13:36,740 --> 00:13:38,577
You can see the
dining room clearly.

221
00:13:39,662 --> 00:13:42,835
Which means, doing it this way... hm?

222
00:13:43,545 --> 00:13:46,049
Why is just this spot white?

223
00:13:46,133 --> 00:13:49,222
There, a picture used to
hang there...

224
00:13:49,306 --> 00:13:51,895
but the landlord took it down
and carried it off yesterday.

225
00:13:52,813 --> 00:13:55,234
This is...
Inspector Megure.

226
00:13:55,527 --> 00:13:56,946
Come here, quickly.

227
00:14:08,685 --> 00:14:10,981
From inside Suzuki's
shoe cubby...

228
00:14:11,064 --> 00:14:13,027
this towel was found.

229
00:14:14,029 --> 00:14:16,993
I see, so that's how it was.

230
00:14:17,786 --> 00:14:20,416
The culprit is Suzuki,
just as I thought. It's you.

231
00:14:21,794 --> 00:14:25,468
You and Katsuko were
on bad terms to begin with.

232
00:14:25,719 --> 00:14:30,812
And tonight's fight pushed it over the
edge, so you killed Katsuko upstairs.

233
00:14:31,396 --> 00:14:34,612
At that time, you wrapped the
knife handle in this towel...

234
00:14:34,695 --> 00:14:36,448
so no fingerprints
would be left.

235
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:41,166
You hid this away, planning
to dispose of it later.

236
00:14:41,751 --> 00:14:44,507
- That settles it, Inspector.
- Yes.

237
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:49,934
Hidehisa Suzuki, would you accompany us
to the station as a person of interest?

238
00:14:50,101 --> 00:14:53,232
It wasn't me. I didn't do it...

239
00:14:53,566 --> 00:14:54,610
That's wrong.

240
00:14:54,694 --> 00:14:56,614
This man is not the culprit.

241
00:14:56,864 --> 00:15:00,497
The culprit is one of these two...
Oh.

242
00:15:06,133 --> 00:15:07,970
So that's how it is.

243
00:15:09,347 --> 00:15:12,938
Ugh, ha-nyo, ha-hii-fuu...

244
00:15:14,692 --> 00:15:16,486
Please wait, everyone.

245
00:15:16,821 --> 00:15:19,409
M... Mr. Mouri? Could it be?

246
00:15:20,161 --> 00:15:22,583
It's too early to declare
Suzuki the culprit...

247
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:23,918
just yet.

248
00:15:24,210 --> 00:15:27,383
B... but Mouri, just now you...

249
00:15:27,467 --> 00:15:30,056
I'm truly ashamed
of myself.

250
00:15:30,473 --> 00:15:33,938
One look at Suzuki and
it should've been obvious.

251
00:15:34,732 --> 00:15:37,028
Recall the scene of the murder.

252
00:15:37,529 --> 00:15:40,535
Katsuko died with her
artery severed...

253
00:15:40,619 --> 00:15:43,457
and blood was splattered
all around the area.

254
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:45,504
And yet, take a look.

255
00:15:45,587 --> 00:15:47,883
Suzuki's sweatshirt
is pure white.

256
00:15:49,052 --> 00:15:52,391
Could the culprit possibly
have avoided getting any blood on them?

257
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:56,483
What if he changed clothes and then
pretended to find the body?

258
00:15:56,901 --> 00:15:58,237
If that were the case...

259
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:00,909
those clothes would have
already been found.

260
00:16:01,243 --> 00:16:03,288
He'd have had no time
to go dispose of them.

261
00:16:03,581 --> 00:16:05,042
You're... right.

262
00:16:05,126 --> 00:16:07,255
Then who is the culprit...

263
00:16:08,298 --> 00:16:10,386
The culprit's actions
were these.

264
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:12,933
First, pretending to be Katsuko...

265
00:16:13,016 --> 00:16:16,481
they wrote a message addressed
to Suzuki on the message board.

266
00:16:17,233 --> 00:16:21,158
To pin Suzuki down in his own
room at the time of the crime...

267
00:16:21,241 --> 00:16:23,287
and strip him of an alibi.

268
00:16:24,247 --> 00:16:27,003
Then, at the time of the murder...

269
00:16:27,211 --> 00:16:29,884
the culprit slipped out of the
bath and went to the second floor.

270
00:16:30,384 --> 00:16:32,263
Hold on a moment, Mouri.

271
00:16:32,346 --> 00:16:37,566
By Ran's testimony, no one passed
through the hallway at the time of the crime.

272
00:16:37,858 --> 00:16:40,237
- Conan.
- Yes.

273
00:16:40,321 --> 00:16:43,493
Detective Takagi, in front
of that door...

274
00:16:43,578 --> 00:16:45,749
there's a large potted
plant, right?

275
00:16:45,832 --> 00:16:49,380
Look at the floor underneath.
There's a mark where it was moved.

276
00:16:49,464 --> 00:16:50,884
Ah.
Just like that mark...

277
00:16:50,967 --> 00:16:53,388
move it a little toward the door.

278
00:16:53,472 --> 00:16:56,979
Ugh, like this?
Then step out into the hallway...

279
00:16:57,063 --> 00:16:59,526
and close the door for me?
Got it.

280
00:17:00,236 --> 00:17:03,450
Now, Ran, go over
to the fridge...

281
00:17:03,534 --> 00:17:07,124
and when I give the signal,
open the fridge door.

282
00:17:07,208 --> 00:17:08,711
Okay, got it.

283
00:17:08,795 --> 00:17:10,256
Everyone, come over here.

284
00:17:13,136 --> 00:17:15,558
Watch Detective Takagi closely.

285
00:17:16,769 --> 00:17:19,190
All right, Ran, open
the fridge door.

286
00:17:19,274 --> 00:17:20,276
Okay.

287
00:17:22,029 --> 00:17:24,033
Th... this is...

288
00:17:24,117 --> 00:17:25,369
How about it?

289
00:17:25,452 --> 00:17:29,795
From where Ran was sitting,
Detective Takagi disappeared from view.

290
00:17:31,006 --> 00:17:34,429
I heard from Conan that around
the time of the crime...

291
00:17:34,638 --> 00:17:37,811
the fridge door was opened twice.

292
00:17:39,606 --> 00:17:42,779
To take out and put back
Katsuko's cake.

293
00:17:43,781 --> 00:17:46,620
Before the crime, the culprit
shifted that potted plant...

294
00:17:46,704 --> 00:17:49,668
while Ran was away
in the bathroom.

295
00:17:50,419 --> 00:17:53,342
And then quietly
slipped out of the bath.

296
00:17:53,968 --> 00:17:55,555
There's proof of that too.

297
00:17:56,515 --> 00:17:58,393
In the changing room...

298
00:17:58,477 --> 00:18:00,815
the culprit stepped in
the spilled shampoo.

299
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:04,322
Those traces were left
in the hallway.

300
00:18:04,740 --> 00:18:08,664
Then, in the brief moment the
fridge door was opened...

301
00:18:08,748 --> 00:18:10,794
the culprit headed for
Katsuko's room.

302
00:18:12,004 --> 00:18:15,094
There, Katsuko, who'd been
given sleeping pills...

303
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:17,056
was fast asleep.

304
00:18:17,682 --> 00:18:19,352
The culprit crept in and...

305
00:18:24,445 --> 00:18:28,871
After the crime, the culprit put the
bloody towel in Suzuki's shoe cubby...

306
00:18:29,122 --> 00:18:33,548
then, the next moment the cake was
being returned to the fridge...

307
00:18:34,591 --> 00:18:38,056
After that, they just had to
return the pot when no one was looking.

308
00:18:38,306 --> 00:18:39,601
Wait, Dad.

309
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:41,020
Then I was...

310
00:18:41,187 --> 00:18:43,108
Ran, you...

311
00:18:43,191 --> 00:18:45,780
were used to create the alibi.

312
00:18:45,947 --> 00:18:48,368
The guest always sits there.

313
00:18:48,911 --> 00:18:52,334
Wait. I'm the one who
opened the fridge.

314
00:18:52,418 --> 00:18:55,884
Which means... the culprit
is Yasuko?

315
00:18:57,261 --> 00:19:01,019
I'm the culprit? That's absurd.
You're wrong.

316
00:19:01,436 --> 00:19:05,068
Huh? Miss, isn't your
shoulder injured?

317
00:19:05,152 --> 00:19:06,362
There's blood
seeping through.

318
00:19:10,497 --> 00:19:11,540
That's the very...

319
00:19:11,624 --> 00:19:14,003
proof that you went
up to the second floor.

320
00:19:14,671 --> 00:19:15,757
Take a look.

321
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:18,011
At that window facing
the staircase.

322
00:19:19,515 --> 00:19:23,396
Though it's up high, when committing
the crime, Yasuko...

323
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,527
didn't want to be seen.

324
00:19:26,027 --> 00:19:30,494
So she crouched down, passed by smoothly,
and when she tried to stand back up...

325
00:19:30,578 --> 00:19:31,580
(snagging sound)

326
00:19:32,582 --> 00:19:35,337
Yes. On the wall past
the window...

327
00:19:35,420 --> 00:19:38,886
exactly at shoulder height,
a nail was sticking out.

328
00:19:39,555 --> 00:19:41,684
Please wait. You...

329
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:45,107
said Suzuki had no
blood spatter on him, right?

330
00:19:45,190 --> 00:19:49,115
But there's no blood of Katsuko's
on my clothes either, is there?

331
00:19:49,908 --> 00:19:52,622
The moment I saw that wound,
I understood right away.

332
00:19:53,290 --> 00:19:56,296
The nail injured your body...

333
00:19:56,379 --> 00:19:58,634
but that T-shirt isn't torn.

334
00:19:59,218 --> 00:20:03,310
The clothes you wore before this
probably weren't torn either.

335
00:20:04,020 --> 00:20:05,982
What does this mean?

336
00:20:06,775 --> 00:20:10,867
After going to the bath, you
stripped off all your clothes...

337
00:20:12,036 --> 00:20:15,167
and killed Katsuko
while completely naked.

338
00:20:15,877 --> 00:20:18,841
(panting)

339
00:20:22,932 --> 00:20:24,978
In that case, the blood spatter...

340
00:20:25,062 --> 00:20:28,569
you wiped off roughly with the towel
you used to hold the knife...

341
00:20:28,653 --> 00:20:33,537
then, being careful not to leave any
traces on the floor, returned to the bath...

342
00:20:33,621 --> 00:20:35,750
and just washed it all
off in the shower.

343
00:20:36,209 --> 00:20:38,171
You're wrong. I...

344
00:20:38,631 --> 00:20:39,716
In that case...

345
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:42,054
shall we have the bath's
drainpipe examined?

346
00:20:42,847 --> 00:20:46,312
Katsuko's blood is surely
going to be detected.

347
00:20:48,358 --> 00:20:50,153
Ah... ah...

348
00:20:51,072 --> 00:20:53,159
Aaah.

349
00:20:53,451 --> 00:20:55,832
Yasuko, why?

350
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:58,879
Click, click, click, click...
it kept echoing down.

351
00:20:58,963 --> 00:21:03,806
From right above me, every night,
every night, the sound of her tap shoes.

352
00:21:03,889 --> 00:21:06,269
No matter how many times I asked,
she wouldn't stop.

353
00:21:07,104 --> 00:21:09,066
I just couldn't take it anymore.

354
00:21:10,152 --> 00:21:11,864
Over something like that...

355
00:21:13,701 --> 00:21:15,412
She said it to me.

356
00:21:15,705 --> 00:21:18,251
"You know, it actually
feels really good."

357
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:21,925
"Like I'm stomping on you
from right over your head."

358
00:21:22,426 --> 00:21:24,430
"So just put up with it."

359
00:21:24,765 --> 00:21:27,812
"A third-rate, unremarkable
woman like you..."

360
00:21:28,438 --> 00:21:32,446
"that's about all you're
ever good for to me."

361
00:21:33,239 --> 00:21:39,251
(Yasuko sobbing)

362
00:21:40,922 --> 00:21:46,934
♪~

363
00:22:54,945 --> 00:23:00,455
~♪

364
00:23:01,290 --> 00:23:02,710
Hey, hey, Dad.

365
00:23:03,044 --> 00:23:05,131
I just thought of
a great idea.

366
00:23:05,883 --> 00:23:08,555
Huh?
Let's make our place a share house too.

367
00:23:08,639 --> 00:23:10,266
It'd help the budget.

368
00:23:10,350 --> 00:23:12,062
What nonsense are you...

369
00:23:12,437 --> 00:23:15,235
I see. And here we have a...

370
00:23:15,318 --> 00:23:17,991
beautiful career woman who
earns a great living.

371
00:23:18,074 --> 00:23:20,286
Hm?
What a shame, what a shame.

372
00:23:20,370 --> 00:23:21,623
(clears throat)

373
00:23:21,707 --> 00:23:24,378
Well, if it helps the
budget even a little...

374
00:23:24,587 --> 00:23:26,591
Really? Yes!

375
00:23:26,675 --> 00:23:29,138
Then I'll go post this in
the empty room.

376
00:23:29,304 --> 00:23:30,306
Hm?

377
00:23:30,390 --> 00:23:32,854
This way the family can
live together again.

378
00:23:32,937 --> 00:23:34,566
I have to call Mom.

379
00:23:34,649 --> 00:23:38,072
H... hey, Ran, stop. Give me that.

380
00:23:38,156 --> 00:23:39,951
Oh, hello, Mom?
Wait.

381
00:23:40,035 --> 00:23:42,330
Hahaha... wait, hold on.

382
00:23:42,414 --> 00:23:44,627
Ms. Kisaki's cooking is...

383
00:23:45,211 --> 00:23:49,428
Aaah, wait, wait.
Ran, please, wait.

384
00:23:51,307 --> 00:23:52,309
Huh?

385
00:23:53,687 --> 00:23:56,985
Here, a printed-out photo. Good luck.

386
00:23:57,612 --> 00:23:59,741
Right. That was 15 years ago.

387
00:24:00,408 --> 00:24:02,622
At another rental cabin
near here...

388
00:24:03,499 --> 00:24:06,630
When the officers rushed in
after hearing the commotion...

389
00:24:07,924 --> 00:24:08,926
Red...

390
00:24:09,176 --> 00:24:10,178
Red...

391
00:24:10,888 --> 00:24:11,932
Red...

392
00:24:12,558 --> 00:24:13,811
Inside the bathtub.

413
00:24:15,211 --> 00:24:16,611
Next Conan,

414
00:24:16,611 --> 00:24:20,611
"The Tragedy of the Red Woman (Bath Steam)"

415
00:24:36,143 --> 00:24:38,610
Next Conan's Hint:

416
00:24:38,611 --> 00:24:40,611
"Tomato".

395
00:24:40,898 --> 00:24:42,524
- Greengrocer. 
- Woodpecker.

396
00:24:42,608 --> 00:24:44,100
Newspaper.
Conan's a weird kid.
397
00:24:44,401 --> 00:24:47,001
Wha...
